WEBVTT

p01
00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:02.340
Open Marketing and look down the left rail.

p02
00:00:02.696 --> 00:00:05.125
Campaigns and Automation you already know.

p03
00:00:05.616 --> 00:00:07.718
Everything under them is what we map today.

p04
00:00:08.306 --> 00:00:10.163
Think of this list as a lookup table:

p05
00:00:10.556 --> 00:00:14.378
a client asks a question, and one of these pages holds the answer.

p06
00:00:14.866 --> 00:00:17.027
By the end you'll go straight to the right one.

p07
00:00:17.440 --> 00:00:18.065
First, SmartLinks.

p08
00:00:18.065 --> 00:00:22.617
These are trackable links you drop into an email or a social post.

p09
00:00:22.617 --> 00:00:27.120
When a manager asks whether that link actually brought cars through the bay,

p10
00:00:27.120 --> 00:00:28.413
you don't guess.

p11
00:00:28.413 --> 00:00:31.852
The page counts clicks, conversions, and the revenue each link earned.

p12
00:00:32.320 --> 00:00:33.349
Next, Customer Segments.

p13
00:00:33.349 --> 00:00:36.216
A segment is just a saved audience,

p14
00:00:36.216 --> 00:00:40.331
a group like win-back or VIP that a campaign gets pointed at.

p15
00:00:40.331 --> 00:00:45.487
So when someone asks who a message went to, the trail ends here.

p16
00:00:45.487 --> 00:00:48.572
Every campaign starts from a list on this page.

p17
00:00:49.040 --> 00:00:50.676
Offers and Promotions.

p18
00:00:51.717 --> 00:00:53.380
This is where the discounts live.

p19
00:00:53.863 --> 00:00:55.766
A member says their promo code bounced?

p20
00:00:56.200 --> 00:00:57.010
Open the offer, check the dates it's valid, and check its status.

p21
00:00:57.304 --> 00:01:03.088
Nine times out of ten the code simply expired.

p22
00:01:03.520 --> 00:01:04.657
Email Templates.

p23
00:01:05.216 --> 00:01:10.725
These are the reusable email layouts the campaigns and the automated lifecycle flows draw from.

p24
00:01:11.383 --> 00:01:12.567
They're sorted by moment: cancellation, refund, plan change, retention.

p25
00:01:12.852 --> 00:01:15.999
When a client asks what the cancellation email says,

p26
00:01:16.707 --> 00:01:21.848
you read it right here, without touching send.

p27
00:01:22.385 --> 00:01:25.033
Paid Media, and notice the draft tag on it.

p28
00:01:25.819 --> 00:01:29.385
This one matches your members to ad accounts on Meta and Google,

p29
00:01:29.743 --> 00:01:32.819
then ties the ad spend back to actual washes.

p30
00:01:33.217 --> 00:01:35.340
It's powerful and it's still being built.

p31
00:01:35.960 --> 00:01:39.938
Read the tabs, but do not click Sync Now or a row Sync.

p32
00:01:40.412 --> 00:01:43.032
Those push audience data out to the ad platforms.

p33
00:01:43.600 --> 00:01:47.090
Now the page every technician should bookmark: Deliverability.

p34
00:01:47.736 --> 00:01:51.270
Before you ever write "the platform didn't send," come here.

p35
00:01:51.734 --> 00:01:55.509
Inbox rate, bounces, spam complaints, and the suppression list.

p36
00:01:55.983 --> 00:01:59.466
If an address was suppressed or bounced, the send didn't fail.

p37
00:01:59.809 --> 00:02:01.874
The system did exactly what it was told.

p38
00:02:02.413 --> 00:02:04.875
Click Referral Program, and watch the breadcrumb.

p39
00:02:05.590 --> 00:02:06.993
It jumps you into Settings.

p40
00:02:07.492 --> 00:02:08.888
This is refer-a-friend: the reward the referrer gets, the reward the friend gets,

p41
00:02:09.209 --> 00:02:14.802
and how many referrals each program has driven.

p42
00:02:15.308 --> 00:02:17.617
Same menu, but it lives on the Settings side.

p43
00:02:18.080 --> 00:02:18.739
SMS Templates.

p44
00:02:18.739 --> 00:02:20.576
The text-message versions.

p45
00:02:20.576 --> 00:02:23.791
Watch the character and segment counts here,

p46
00:02:23.791 --> 00:02:28.735
because a text that runs long splits into two segments and costs more to send.

p47
00:02:28.735 --> 00:02:32.313
Short and tight isn't a style choice on S-M-S.

p48
00:02:32.313 --> 00:02:33.520
It's the budget.

p49
00:02:33.920 --> 00:02:36.254
RCS Templates, the richer cousin of texting.

p50
00:02:36.254 --> 00:02:37.718
Cards, carousels, images.

p51
00:02:37.718 --> 00:02:41.051
On a newer phone the member sees the full experience.

p52
00:02:41.051 --> 00:02:45.333
On an older one it quietly drops back to a plain text,

p53
00:02:45.333 --> 00:02:50.000
and the fallback column tells you how often that safety net is in place.

p54
00:02:50.400 --> 00:02:53.140
Mobile Content Blocks, back on the Settings side.

p55
00:02:54.529 --> 00:02:56.701
This is what a customer sees inside the app:

p56
00:02:57.210 --> 00:03:00.032
the promo banner, the card rail, the announcements.

p57
00:03:00.837 --> 00:03:03.228
It's a live editor, so treat it gently.

p58
00:03:03.764 --> 00:03:04.732
Read the layout.

p59
00:03:04.952 --> 00:03:06.675
Do not click Save and Publish.

p60
00:03:07.200 --> 00:03:07.917
Last one, Push Campaigns.

p61
00:03:08.117 --> 00:03:09.125
This is where the app's push notifications get written and scheduled,

p62
00:03:09.417 --> 00:03:15.797
with a preview of how they'll look on a lock screen.

p63
00:03:16.051 --> 00:03:18.947
It's a compose-and-send surface, so we only name it.

p64
00:03:19.249 --> 00:03:22.301
Do not start a new campaign and do not publish.

p65
00:03:22.520 --> 00:03:23.818
Read it and move on.

p66
00:03:24.240 --> 00:03:25.409
That's the whole menu.

p67
00:03:25.755 --> 00:03:29.955
Links to SmartLinks, audiences to Segments, discounts to Offers,

p68
00:03:30.299 --> 00:03:31.931
wording to the template pages, ad matching to Paid Media, and inbox health to Deliverability.

p69
00:03:32.245 --> 00:03:35.893
Learn the map now, so when a client's win-back texts go quiet in one town,

p70
00:03:36.316 --> 00:03:44.635
you already know the two pages that explain it before anyone files a bug.

